New Records: Austria secured their first win in a competitive group stage of a major tournament after a thrilling 3-2 victory over the Netherlands, capping their impressive run in Euro 2024
Key Match Events: Marcel Sabitzer scored the 80th-minute winner with a composed finish after Christoph Baumgartner's through ball
Austria came back from 2-0 down to defeat the Netherlands
Pre-Game Insights: Ralf Rangnick made several changes to his starting lineup, including bringing in Christoph Baumgartner and Konrad Laimer, showcasing his tactical flexibility
Austria's attacking fluidity and technical ability were highlighted as key strengths before the match
Post-Match Reflections: Ronald Koeman admitted the Netherlands' poor performance and lack of pressure
Ralf Rangnick praised his team's resilience and depth, especially after key players like David Alaba and Xaver Schlager were absent
Miscellaneous Highlights: Austria's win solidified their reputation as a strong contender in the tournament
Sabitzer's performance at the peak of his career was a standout moment
Austria's next match in the knockout stage is against the runner-up of Group F, adding excitement to their journey
Others: Austria will face the runner-up of Group F in the last 16 on July 2, 2024
